complaints.summary: Sept 4 2024 my husband was involved in a motor vehicle accident involving a gravel hauler that hit him twice once in the rear then in drivers side that cause my husband to spin out of control hitting another vehicle  none of the airbags deployed  My husband should have been killed or severely injured by the grace of God he was not

The contact owns a 2022 Cadillac CT4. The contact stated that while driving approximately 60-65 MPH, the power steering and power brakes failed to operate as needed. The check engine and the crash warning lights were illuminated. The contact coasted to the side of the road while depressing the brake pedal with an excessive amount of force. The vehicle was stopped by bumping on a nearby curb. Once the vehicle was stopped, the contact turned off and restarted the vehicle and was able to regain power steering and power brakes functionality. The check engine warning light remained illuminated. The failure had occurred twice. The vehicle was taken to the dealer where it was diagnosed that the vehicle was showing 24 failed Communication codes; however, the exact cause of failure was unknown. The battery was replaced by the dealer after the first failure however, after the failure recurred no additional repairs had been performed. The manufacturer was made aware of the failure a complaint was filed. The contact was referred to the dealer for further assistance. The failure mileage was 9,000.

The problem first arose in June 2023. I was driving and suddenly, all the dashboard lights went on and the brakes stopped working. There was no pressure on the pedal. I was able to roll to a stop without incident. I turned the car off and back on again and the brakes worked but the check engine light was still on. I was able to limp the mile back to my house. After almost 6 weeks at the dealer, I was told they replaced a brake module and the car was fine. On [XXX], it happened again. It was towed to the dealer and I refused to drive it again. The car had about 2400 miles on it. They took it back, although claiming nothing was wrong, and I bought the CT4V Blackwing 2023 VIN [XXX] . On [XXX], it happened in the new car (500 miles on it). The dashboard lit up, the brakes wouldn't work, although this time instead of no pressure on the pedal, it was hard as a rock. After turning it on and off again, the brakes worked but the speed was restricted and other things in the car did not seem to be working correctly. The check engine light was also on. The dealership towed it. They told me they could not recreate the problem. Weeks later, I was told that an engineer from GM was looking at it. I received a call from some customer support department person who eventually told me that there was nothing wrong with the car, that the brake failure was a result of the Allstate Milewise device that was plugged in and they would not do anything for me. My husband has a Milewise in his Chevy truck with no issues. I found a forum online discussing this problem which has apparently happened to numerous people in CT4V and Blackwings. I also spoke to Allstate which does not have any reported problems with the device.  INFORMATION REDACTED PURSUANT TO THE FREEDOM OF INFORMATION ACT (FOIA), 5 U.S.C. 552(B)(6)

While driving in normal street conditions, the dashboard lit up and all the lights came on. Traction control, stability control, check engine light, tire pressure, brake, ABS all lit up. The digital dash showed two errors: 1. Forward Collision System Unavailable and 2. Steering assist is reduced, drive with care. I noticed that steering became much more difficult and braking was extremely difficult. When coasting to a park, my car would not engage the e-brake unless I shut the car down at first and then re-started it. This is the second time this has happened to me, the first time was 4 months ago and the Cadillac dealership already tried to fix the problem by replacing a brake control module. Clearly they did not fix it and now I do not feel safe in the vehicle. The problem is not easily reproducible as it comes on randomly while driving (I was literally cruising in 5th gear). My car is a manual transmission if that makes a difference, so the e-brake is pretty vital. Uploaded are pictures from 4 months ago when the problem first happened and I was stopped at my house. The last picture was from yesterday while I was driving and the issue re-occurred. I have dropped off my car today at the dealership for them to look at again.

A few days ago while driving (45mph), my 22' 4BW dash lit up like hell and I lost power steering, brakes, went into limp mode. Restarted the vehicle, all was well. I did almost take out the Mini Cooper in front of me, with a 'Baby on Board' sticker. Don't even want to think about that. I have a service appointment scheduled for next week and I'm not driving the vehicle until then.  Please review the following thread on the Blackwing forums where over 7 different people experience the same issue within 7 days of each other.  https://www.cadillacvnet.com/forums/threads/ct4bws-turning-off-safety-risk.3928/#post-75520  Dealers are not taking responsibility for this issue and we are afraid to drive our cars.

While driving at higher speeds the multiple CT4 vehicles that I have driven share steering issues. While driving straight, there are no issues. If following gentle bends in the highway to the RIGHT, randomly the vehicles will increase the force required to maintain the current ground track. This causes the vehicle to slightly pull away from the desired track to the left. It does NOT occur when steering to the left, only to the right. It feels as if the steering enters a different type of steering mode and eases the required steering wheel pressure when the vehicle returns to straight driving. The fact that this steering is sour is randomly timed, only occurs in one direction leads me to believe that it irks an engineering problem. I have found this issue to present itself on the CT4 and CT5. I have personally driven the vehicles as well as confirmed the issue with sources online. I do not feel that this issues constitutes a safe steering feedback.

issues.title: Supercharger Heat Soak and Performance Loss
issues.description: The LT4 supercharged engine experiences heat soak during extended high-performance driving, leading to reduced power output and potential limp mode activation. The intercooler system struggles to maintain optimal charge air temperatures under sustained load.
symptoms: Power reduction after extended spirited driving
Higher than normal intake air temperatures
issues.fix_description: Aftermarket intercooler upgrade, improved cooling system modifications, or ECU tuning to manage heat more effectively
issues.prevention: Allow proper cool-down periods between track sessions, avoid sustained high-RPM operation in hot weather

issues.title: Carbon Fiber Hood Delamination
issues.description: The carbon fiber hood panel experiences delamination where the carbon fiber separates from the underlying substrate, particularly around the edges and heat-exposed areas near the supercharger heat extractor.
symptoms: Visible separation of carbon fiber layers
Bubbling or lifting of hood surface
issues.fix_description: Hood replacement under warranty or aftermarket carbon fiber hood installation
issues.prevention: Park in shade when possible, use hood covers during storage, avoid pressure washing directly on hood seams

issues.title: Transmission Overheating During Track Use
issues.description: The 10-speed automatic transmission overheats during extended track sessions, causing harsh shifting, delayed engagement, and potential transmission protection mode activation.
issues.fix_description: Install aftermarket transmission cooler, upgrade transmission fluid to higher performance specification, or software recalibration
issues.prevention: Monitor transmission temperatures during track use, take cool-down breaks, consider manual mode for better control

issues.title: Brembo Brake Squeal and Glazing
issues.description: The high-performance Brembo brake pads produce excessive noise during normal driving and are prone to glazing when not properly heated, reducing braking effectiveness.
symptoms: Glazed appearance on brake pad surface
issues.fix_description: Replace with different compound brake pads suited for street driving, or properly bed-in existing pads
issues.prevention: Perform proper brake bed-in procedure, warm brakes gradually, avoid aggressive braking when cold

issues.title: Infotainment System Freezing and Slow Response
issues.description: The CUE infotainment system experiences frequent freezing, slow response times, and occasional complete system crashes requiring hard resets.
issues.fix_description: Software updates from dealership, system reset procedures, or infotainment module replacement if under warranty
issues.prevention: Keep software updated, avoid using system during extreme temperatures, perform regular system resets

issues.title: Fuel System Vapor Lock Issues
issues.description: High-performance driving in hot weather can cause fuel system vapor lock, leading to fuel starvation and engine stumbling, particularly during sustained high-G cornering or acceleration.
symptoms: Engine hesitation or stumbling under acceleration
issues.fix_description: Fuel system modifications including upgraded fuel pumps, lines, or tank ventilation improvements
issues.prevention: Keep fuel tank at least half full during track use, avoid prolonged high-performance driving in extreme heat

issues.title: Rear Differential Noise and Whining
issues.description: The electronic limited-slip differential develops noise, whining, or clicking sounds, particularly during low-speed turns or when the differential is actively engaging.
issues.fix_description: Differential fluid change with proper specification fluid, or differential rebuild/replacement if severely damaged
issues.prevention: Regular differential service, avoid aggressive launches on high-traction surfaces, use proper differential fluid

issues.title: Paint Quality Issues and Chipping
issues.description: Paint quality concerns including premature chipping, particularly on the front bumper and hood edges, and inconsistent paint finish quality from the factory.
issues.fix_description: Paint correction, touch-up work, or panel repainting depending on severity
issues.prevention: Apply paint protection film, regular washing and waxing, park away from high-debris areas

issues.title: Air Conditioning Compressor Failure
issues.description: Premature air conditioning compressor failure, particularly in vehicles subjected to high ambient temperatures or extended track use where the AC system works harder.
issues.fix_description: AC compressor replacement, system evacuation and recharge, check for underlying cooling system issues
issues.prevention: Regular AC system maintenance, avoid running AC at maximum load continuously, address cooling system issues promptly

issues.title: Tire Pressure Monitoring System Malfunctions
issues.description: TPMS sensors provide false readings or fail completely, particularly after track use where tire temperatures and pressures fluctuate significantly.
issues.fix_description: TPMS sensor replacement, system relearning procedure, or sensor battery replacement
issues.prevention: Avoid extreme temperature cycling, proper sensor maintenance during tire changes, regular system checks

editorial.tagline: American muscle sedan meets German precision engineering
editorial.hero_blurb: The CT4-V Blackwing represents Cadillac's swan song to naturally-aspirated V8 performance sedans, delivering 472 horsepower through a screaming twin-turbo V6. This is the last of its kind - a manual transmission, rear-wheel-drive luxury missile that refuses to compromise.
editorial.essence: The CT4-V Blackwing is Cadillac's final answer to BMW M3 and Mercedes-AMG C63 dominance. It combines old-school American muscle car philosophy with modern chassis dynamics and luxury appointments, creating something uniquely compelling in the shrinking performance sedan segment.
editorial.heritage: Born from Cadillac's V-Series lineage that began with the 2004 CTS-V, the Blackwing badge represents the pinnacle of Cadillac performance engineering. The CT4-V Blackwing carries forward the brand's commitment to rear-wheel-drive sport sedans in an era when most manufacturers are abandoning the formula.
editorial.design_philosophy: Cadillac's designers focused on creating an uncompromising driver's car that balances track capability with daily usability. The aggressive bodywork serves function over form, with every vent, wing, and spoiler designed to manage airflow and cooling during hard driving.
editorial.motorsport_history: While the CT4-V Blackwing itself hasn't raced extensively, it inherits DNA from Cadillac's successful V-Series.R GT3 program and the brand's IMSA DPi championship efforts. The Blackwing development team utilized lessons learned from professional motorsports to create the most track-focused Cadillac sedan ever.
editorial.engine_character: The twin-turbo 3.6L V6 delivers power with relentless urgency, building boost quickly and pulling hard to redline. Unlike some turbo engines that feel lazy, this unit responds immediately to throttle inputs with a linear, naturally-aspirated feel despite the forced induction.
editorial.transmission_feel: The available 6-speed manual transmission offers crisp, mechanical shifts with perfectly weighted throws. The clutch engagement is progressive and confidence-inspiring, making heel-toe downshifts a joy even in stop-and-go traffic.
editorial.chassis_dynamics: Magnetic Ride Control suspension adapts instantly to changing conditions, providing GT car comfort in Tour mode and track-ready stiffness in Track mode. The chassis balance favors slight oversteer, encouraging spirited driving while remaining controllable at the limit.
editorial.steering_feel: The steering provides excellent road feel with variable assist that lightens for parking but weights up beautifully at speed. Turn-in is immediate and precise, with enough feedback to communicate exactly what the front tires are doing.
editorial.brake_confidence: Brembo 4-piston front calipers provide exceptional stopping power with excellent pedal feel. The brakes resist fade even during repeated hard stops, inspiring confidence on both street and track.
editorial.sound_signature: The twin-turbo V6 produces a sophisticated growl that builds to an angry snarl under acceleration. While not as melodic as a naturally-aspirated V8, the soundtrack is distinctly aggressive and purposeful, especially with the available performance exhaust.
editorial.ideal_owner: Driving enthusiasts who want a practical four-door that can embarrass supercars on weekends. Perfect for buyers who appreciate manual transmissions, rear-wheel-drive dynamics, and the exclusivity of owning one of the last true performance sedans.
editorial.not_ideal_for: Buyers seeking maximum fuel economy, those who prefer all-wheel-drive security, or anyone wanting a quiet, comfortable luxury cruiser. The firm suspension and aggressive nature make it less suitable for pure comfort-focused buyers.
editorial.buyers_summary: The CT4-V Blackwing represents exceptional value in the performance sedan space, offering supercar-level acceleration and track capability for significantly less money than German rivals. Buy now before they're gone - this formula won't be repeated.

SUBJECT: Cadillac CT4-V Blackwing (2022-2024), pristine showroom condition.

SETTING: Private collector's industrial warehouse garage. Brick warehouse with arched windows OR modern concrete gallery OR vintage factory with timber beams.

COMPOSITION: Front 3/4 hero angle showing front fascia and driver's side profile. Show COMPLETE car (all four wheels, both bumpers, full roofline). Camera at knee height.

LIGHTING: Golden hour sunlight streaming through large industrial windows. Warm color temperature. Cinematic depth.

TECHNICAL: Magazine-quality automotive photography. Photorealistic, no CGI look. No people, no text, no watermarks, no logos, no license plates.
